The alert generation system main purpose is to evaluate the incoming data and route alerts to the medical staff if needed.
Each patient can have different thresholds for different measurement types, because it depends on the individual.
If a measurement value of a patient is higher than their accepted threshold,
the alert generation system writes it out on console and uploads it to a special Tcp server, which uses the first port.
The alert generator is the controller in the alert generation system, it monitorize patient data and triggers an alert generation process
if a measurement value is over the threshold. It uses the alert manager to do it. The alert manager can notify staff with writing out the alert on console,
and upload the alert data to the Tcp server. In healthcare documentation is very important, this is a main reason for uploading alerts to the server.
One alert has a patient Id, a condition and a timestamp. These variables are private, however can seeable through getters.
The Alert Manager has its own private Tcp and console output strategies and they are not accessible from outside of the class.
The Alert Generator has its own private alert manager, however it has a getter.
